  "prompt": "Which Pakistani universities are recognized by Australian immigration department?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the recognition of Pakistani universities by the Australian immigration department can change based on various agreements and evaluations. Australian institutions generally refer to lists such as the Pakistan Higher Education Commission (HEC) recognized universities, but for precise and up-to-date information, it is best to refer directly to the Australian Government Department of Home Affairs or consult the latest guidelines by organizations like the Australian Education International (AEI).\n\nTypically, universities such as the University of the Punjab, Lahore; National University of Sciences and Technology (NUST), Islamabad; Quaid-i-Azam University, Islamabad; and Lahore University of Management Sciences (LUMS) are among the well-recognized institutions.\n\nFor the most current and specific information, you may want to visit the official website of the Australian Department of Home Affairs or contact them directly.",
